{"message": "I am incredibly disappointed that you haven't moved a single cent toward a fair market value. Expecting a nearly 50% discount on premium, retail-grade equipment under the guise of a 'budget' is simply not how business works. I have been more than generous with my $25.00 offer, which—as I mentioned—is already a massive favor to you.

My other buyer is literally waiting for my confirmation to pay the full $26.00 right now. I am holding them off because I wanted to help your education center, but I cannot justify losing money because of your rigidness. 

As an absolute final gesture of goodwill, I will drop to $24.50. This is an unheard-of price for 50 premium pens. If you cannot meet me there immediately, I am ending this negotiation and selling to the other party who actually recognizes the value of quality tools. This is your last chance to get these for your students. Do we have a deal or not?", "price": 24.5}
